name: The Wrong Time
description: Osyraa, the fearsome Orion leader, has traveled back to Earth's past, hoping to make a name for herself in an easier time. Determine the extent of the damage and find a way to stop her!
rules:
-- There are two Phases to this Event! Each Phase is individually timed.
-- In this Hybrid Event, you will complete Faction Missions in one phase, and Supply Missions in another phase.
-- Unique Faction Missions and Supply Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using any version of Osyraa, Guinan, Pulaski, or Brutal crew will provide a bonus to Faction Missions and Supply Missions.
-- Every Faction or Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- Community Rewards are also available during Phase 2 only. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Osyraa, Guinan, Pulaski, or Brutal
rewards_teaser: Reach Rank 1 by gaining Victory Points from Event Missions!

featured_crew.name: Xindi-Aquatic
featured_crew.flavor: As part of the Xindi council, the Xindi-Aquatic councilor debates with Archer over whether they were lied to by the Sphere Builders.

featured_crew.name: Guinan
featured_crew.flavor: Guinan, contemporary to this time period, meets Picard for the “first” time as he tries to prevent Data’s murder.

rewards.flavor: 10 valuable items. Go to Time Portal to collect!

screens.text: "You've heard of Osyraa? If you haven't, you will soon. She couldn't manage to take control of our universe, so she's gone back in time to when it would be easier--Earth, at the turn of the twentieth century."
"This can't be good, obviously, knowing what we know about her. But she's a very determined woman. You almost have to admire her insistence on getting what she wants."

"I don't have to do anything. I'm not a Starfleet officer. But you two are, and I could use a vacation. Let's see just what kind of past Osyraa's creating for your people, and figure out how to fix it."
